Prevalence and intensity of infection: Usually high, with values between 52 % and 100 % in most studies from Egypt , Nigeria and South Africa (
Aderounmu & Adeniyi 1972
;
Shotter 1980
;
Faisal et al . 1989
;
Anosike et al . 1992
;
Barson & Avenant-Oldewage 2006
). In the present study the overall prevalence was 5–17 % in the Sudan , 26 % in Ethiopia and 33 % in Kenya (Appendix 1 ).

